commit.message: Allow base-4.20 and tasty-1.5; bump CI to GHC 9.8
Update README.md CI build badge

Use copyMutableByteArray# in moveByteArray

The primop in question appears to have always been safe for
use with overlapping ranges since its introduction. See also:
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/commit/b00b36196a88ad6b9054244caaec926f6f9db2cf

The cbits function "hsprimitive_memmove" is now unused,
but is not removed because it was arguably publicly exposed
due to the "Install-Includes: primitive-memops.h".
Use copyMutableByteArrayNonOverlapping# when available
Add `byteArrayAsForeignPtr`

Add withPrimArrayContents and withMutablePrimArrayContents (#400)

commit.message: Add changelog entry for #371
Add version to `@since` annotations

Clarify that size and alignment are in bytes

Add example to `sizeOfType`

Add sizeOfType# and alignmentOfType# class methods to Prim

Also adds the lifted variants sizeOfType and alignmentOfType, both of which return a
boxed Int instead of Int#. At a later date, the sizeOf# and alignmentOf# methods will
be deprecated and then removed.
